{"article_id":"5tIfiG1jV0U8gs7L","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"OBAMACARE MEANS NET LOSS OF POLICIES -","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"ObamaCare seems to have been an insurance killer so far .","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"More than 5 million policies were nixed under the law ' s new regulations .","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"Announcing that just over 2 million people are potential paying customers is a rather stunning admission of defeat .","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"Some of the millions may have landed on employer-based insurance","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"and others may have become eligible under the expanded Medicaid program ,","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"but there are evidently many people","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"who do not have coverage today","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"because of the law .","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"[ Deadline :","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"ObamaCare enrollees have until Jan. 10 to pay premiums for coverage retroactive to Jan . 1 . ]","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"WHITE HOUSE NOT SAYING","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"HOW MANY ENROLLED -","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Democrats are talking big numbers :","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"2.1 million applicants for ObamaCare and millions more new enrollees in the welfare program","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"that provides free coverage to the poor ,","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"Medicaid .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"But the Obama administration has so far refused to disclose the number","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"that matters :","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"The number of people","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"who actually have obtained insurance under the law .","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"AP reports ,","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"\" Insurers say","depth":14},{"id":23,"text":"they are receiving thousands of erroneous sign-up applications from the government ,","depth":15},{"id":24,"text":"and some people","depth":18},{"id":25,"text":"who thought","depth":19},{"id":26,"text":"they had enrolled for coverage","depth":19},{"id":27,"text":"have not received confirmation .","depth":17},{"id":28,"text":"Undoubtedly , some will find out","depth":17},{"id":29,"text":"they don ' t have the immediate coverage","depth":18},{"id":30,"text":"they thought","depth":19},{"id":31,"text":"they did. \"","depth":19},{"id":32,"text":"A recent WSJ report revealed","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"only half of enrollees had made their first months payment .","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"The government is touting nearly 4 million","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"who have been \" deemed eligible \" for welfare benefits ,","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"but , again , that ' s not the same as enrollments .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"The silence so far on the real numbers is reminiscent of the quiet","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"that fell over the administration","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"after the enrollment period began on Oct. 1 .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"Do they not know ?","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Scary .","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"Do they not want to say ?","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"Scarier .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"' LIE OF THE YEAR ' ADS ROLL OUT ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"LIKE IT OR NOT -","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"The conservative group Americans for Prosperity announced Wednesday","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"it is greeting three vulnerable Democrats with big ad buys in the New Year .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"The group is spending $ 2.5 million dollars","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"to hit Sens . Kay Hagan , D-N.C. , Mary Landrieu , D-La. , and Jeanne Shaheen , D-N.H. ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"for repeating President Obama ' s \" you can keep it \" pledge ,","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"deemed \" lie of the year \" by PolitiFact .","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"Spin cycle on overdrive -","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"President Obama ' s permanent campaign apparatus , Organizing for Action , has launched its own online ad campaign in an effort","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"to share ObamaCare success stories .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"The White House is also ramping up its PR efforts","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"to put the troubled health law in a more positive light .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"Team Obama is offering social media tools","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"to help spread its \" # GetCovered \" message ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"including Facebook profile images and banners .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"They have also launched a new section on the White House Web site","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"encouraging visitors to submit their own health care success stories .","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"THE HIGH PRICE OF POLITICAL IGNORANCE","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"-","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"George Will considers the consequences of a uninformed electorate in The price of political ignorance : More government .","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"\" Political ignorance helps explain Americans ' perpetual disappointment with politicians generally , and presidents especially ,","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"to whom voters unrealistically attribute abilities","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"to control events .","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"The elections of 1932 and 1980 dramatically illustrated how voters primarily control politicians","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"- by ' retrospective voting ,","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"' refusing to reelect them . \"","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"[ LAT ' s Mark Z. Barabak considers","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"how \" throw the bums out \" so often results in the bums staying exactly where they are . ]","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"PICK SIX :","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"YOUR MIDTERM PREDICTIONS -","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"With control of the Senate within reach of the GOP this year ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"we asked you to play pundit","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"and give us your six picks for the most likely Republican path to a Senate majority .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"The consensus :","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"Arkansas Democrat Mark Pryor is toast .","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"But beyond that , most of you forecast additional GOP pickups in Alaska , Louisiana , Montana , South Dakota and West Virginia .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"Many of you added your thoughts","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"on how the GOP might get there :","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"\" Republicans have to get their ground game to work .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"They need to message themselves as pro-freedom , pro-liberty , and pro-America with real solutions to the failed policies of the past 5 years , \"","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"wrote Daniel Seiler .","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"\" They have the upper hand ,","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"because they have the argument .","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"They just have to be disciplined enough","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"to get it . \"","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"DEMS DRUMMING UP SUPPORT FOR JOBLESS BENEFITS -","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"Sen . Majority Leader Harry Reid says","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"the Senate ' s first order of business will be to resume federal subsidies for extended unemployment benefits","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"when it reconvenes on Monday .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Reid told the AP Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"the Senate will take up a bipartisan measure from Sens . Dean Heller .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"R-Nev. ,","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"and Jack Reed , D-R.I. ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"that extends unemployment benefits for three months .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"has more .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"[ Washington Examiner ' s David Freddoso makes the case","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"against extending unemployment benefits .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"\" In a market with few good jobs available and long-term unemployment benefits , it was rational for earnest job-seekers to hold out for something better than what was there .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"when the issue is forced ,","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"some job is better than no job at all . \" ]","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"Reid ' s jobs plan includes keeping his own","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"-","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"The Hill reports","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"that Reid ' s play on restoring extended payments for the unemployed could be a particular boon to some embattled members of his conference , Sen. Mark Pryor , D-Ark. , and Sen. Kay Hagan , D-N.C , both represent states with higher-than-average unemployment .","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"WITH YOUR SECOND CUP OF COFFEE ...","depth":4},{"id":111,"text":"Graham Allison , the director of the Harvard Kennedy School ' s Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs , poses an uncomfortable question for 2014 :","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Is the stage set for a large-scale war ?","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Not likely ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"he says ,","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"but points out","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"that we ' ve thought that before .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"\" Precisely a hundred years ago","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"[ Wednesday ] ,","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"the richest man in the world sent New Year ' s greetings to a thousand of the most influential leaders in the U.S. and Europe","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"announcing :","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"mission accomplished .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"' International Peace ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"'","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"he proclaimed ,","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"' is to prevail through the Great Powers","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"agreeing to settle their disputes by International Law ,","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"the pen thus proving mightier than the sword. ' \"","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"We know how that turned out , Mr. Carnegie .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"Read it all from The National Interest .","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"Obama Job Approval :","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"Approve","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"- 42.6 percent//Disapprove - 53.4 percent","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"Direction of Country :","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"Right Direction - 30.1 percent//Wrong Track - 63.3 percent","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"Generic Congressional Ballot :","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"Democrats - 43.3 percent// Republicans 43.1 percent","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"BUBBA CHANNELS","depth":3},{"id":138,"text":"ELIZABETH WARREN -","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"In his remarks at the swearing in of New York ' s new Mayor Bill de Blasio , former President Bill Clinton wasn ' t looking for any Third Way out .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"The event featured an invocation","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"that deemed New York a \" plantation \"","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"and was focused on de Blasio ' s call for \" a new progressive direction \" and big tax hikes on top earners .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"Clinton said","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"he \" strongly endorse [ d ] \" de Blasio ' s platform","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"and called the gap between rich and poor in New York a \" moral outrage. \"","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"Former first lady Hillary Clinton did not speak ,","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"but the enthusiastic endorsement by her husband ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"widely distrusted by the Democratic left as too good a friend of Wall Street ,","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"might go even farther","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"in quelling anxieties from those","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"still hoping","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"a liberal challenger will emerge to the party ' s 2016 frontrunner .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"\" I have to say","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"I strongly endorse Bill de Blasio ' s core campaign commitment to shared opportunities , \"","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"the former president , said .","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"\" And this inequality problem bedevils the entire country . \"","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"Did they try stopping and frisking ? -","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"New York Mayor Bill de Blasio took the oath on the same Bible","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"used by fellow New Yorker Franklin Roosevelt in his 1933 presidential inauguration .","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"when the ceremony ended ,","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"the Good Book was gone .","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"A massive search ,","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"that included sifting through garbage ,","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"ended","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"when a NYPD detective uncovered the Bible .","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"NY Post has the story .","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"NO ALOHA SPIRIT FOR HAWAII DEMS -","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"A bitter Senate primary is shaping up in President Obama ' s home state .","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"Gov . Neil Abercrombie ' s , D-Hawaii , appointed former Lt. Gov . Brian Schatz","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"to fill the seat of the late Sen. Daniel Inouye , D-Hawaii ,","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"even though Inouye had made clear before his death in December 2012","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"that he wanted Rep. Colleen Hanabusa , D-Hawaii , to get the gig .","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"Now , Hanabusa is giving up her House seat","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"to challenge Schatz ,","depth":15},{"id":176,"text":"who has won the endorsements of former New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg and former Vice President Al Gore .","depth":15},{"id":177,"text":"Bloomberg is headlining a fundraiser for Schatz today .","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"Hanabusa was a stalwart for Hillary Clinton ,","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"while Schatz was an early booster for Obama .","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"Abercrombie didn ' t help calm things in his interview with WaPo ' s Philip Rucker :","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"Abercrombie said","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"he disagreed with Inouye ' s wishes ,","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"adding","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"that he didn ' t want to ' get into a discussion about letters and deathbed notices. '","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"The governor said","depth":14},{"id":186,"text":"he thought","depth":15},{"id":187,"text":"Hanabusa , now 62 , was too old","depth":16},{"id":188,"text":"to build enough seniority in the Senate","depth":17},{"id":189,"text":"to continue Inouye ' s legacy","depth":18},{"id":190,"text":"of steering an outsize allowance of federal money to Hawaii .","depth":18},{"id":191,"text":"Noting","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"that Inouye entered the Senate in 1963 at age 38 ,","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"Abercrombie said :","depth":15},{"id":194,"text":"' Brian Schatz is 41 .","depth":16},{"id":195,"text":"Colleen isn ' t .","depth":17},{"id":196,"text":"She ' s in her 60s. ' \"","depth":17},{"id":197,"text":"If the acrimony deepens ,","depth":13},{"id":198,"text":"Republicans might actually have a chance in the Aloha State , with former Rep. Charles Djou ready for action .","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"MORE RUMBLINGS ON SPRINGTIME IMMIGRATION PUSH -","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"NYT :","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"\" Speaker John A. Boehner of Ohio has signaled","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"he may embrace a series of limited changes to the nation ' s immigration laws in the coming months ,","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"giving advocates for change new hope","depth":14},{"id":204,"text":"that 2014 might be the year","depth":15},{"id":205,"text":"that a bitterly divided Congress reaches a political compromise","depth":16},{"id":206,"text":"to overhaul the sprawling system . \"","depth":16},{"id":207,"text":"Yes , but... -","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"This sounds like the NYT playing some catch up here .","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"The odds","depth":13},{"id":210,"text":"of Boehner doing anything like \" comprehensive \" immigration changes","depth":13},{"id":211,"text":"look low indeed .","depth":12},{"id":212,"text":"How many anonymous sources in stories like these are just looking to divide GOPers .","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"And how much of this is Boehner playing for time with big business groups","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"demanding action on conditional amnesty for illegals ?","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"SIX CALIFORNIAS -","depth":7},{"id":216,"text":"Is California so large","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"it has become ungovernable ?","depth":10},{"id":218,"text":"That ' s the conclusion of venture capitalist Tim Draper .","depth":9},{"id":219,"text":"Draper ' s solution :","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"create six states out of the Golden State .","depth":11},{"id":221,"text":"According to the venture capitalist ' s proposed ballot initiative ,","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"new states","depth":14},{"id":223,"text":"known as Silicon Valley and West California","depth":14},{"id":224,"text":"would be anchored by the cities of San Francisco and Los Angeles , respectively .","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"South California would include Orange County and San Diego .","depth":13},{"id":226,"text":"Remaining counties would be divided into areas","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"called Central California , North California and Jefferson .","depth":14},{"id":228,"text":"The proposal contends","depth":11},{"id":229,"text":"that the sheer size of the state creates problems for governance ,","depth":12},{"id":230,"text":"its costly media markets make elections expensive ,","depth":13},{"id":231,"text":"and the competing interests of coastal and inland regions promote policies","depth":14},{"id":232,"text":"that only favor certain areas .","depth":14},{"id":233,"text":"[ Walter Russell Mead likes it :","depth":11},{"id":234,"text":"\" We may disagree with the boundaries somewhat ,","depth":12},{"id":235,"text":"but the idea is a sound one-indeed ,","depth":13},{"id":236,"text":"it ' s potentially one of the most important US reform possibilities out there . \" ]","depth":13},{"id":237,"text":"ROB FORD GOING TO HIT IT AGAIN -","depth":7},{"id":238,"text":"Toronto Mayor Rob Ford ,","depth":12},{"id":239,"text":"who gained notoriety in 2013 for his past affinity for crack use and his unruly antics ,","depth":12},{"id":240,"text":"may be grabbing headlines again in 2014 . '","depth":11},{"id":241,"text":"John Roberts got the scoop","depth":11},{"id":242,"text":"that Ford will seek re-election this year .","depth":11},{"id":243,"text":"Ford files today .","depth":9},{"id":244,"text":"Voters in Toronto will elect their next mayor Oct. 27 .","depth":9},{"id":245,"text":"Toronto ' s The Star has more .","depth":9},{"id":246,"text":"HEY HOSER , DON ' T BURN THE DONUTS , EH -","depth":8},{"id":247,"text":"Two men","depth":12},{"id":248,"text":"driving through a remote mountainous section of Alberta , Canada","depth":12},{"id":249,"text":"resorted to some unorthodox methods","depth":11},{"id":250,"text":"to keep warm","depth":11},{"id":251,"text":"when their car became stranded .","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"The Calgary Sun reports","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":254,"text":"with temperatures dropping to 5 degrees ,","depth":16},{"id":255,"text":"the two removed the seats of the Honda","depth":16},{"id":256,"text":"and lit them on fire","depth":16},{"id":257,"text":"to provide warmth ,","depth":16},{"id":258,"text":"later deciding to torch the entire car .","depth":13},{"id":259,"text":"In the morning , they realized","depth":14},{"id":260,"text":"they were in easy walking distance to a home .","depth":14},{"id":261,"text":"That ' s where police found them","depth":15},{"id":262,"text":"after passersby reported the smoke plume from their roadside pyres .","depth":15},{"id":263,"text":"The duo was treated for minor burns and frostbite .","depth":14},{"id":264,"text":"And it turns out","depth":13},{"id":265,"text":"both men were in possession of cell phones .","depth":13},{"id":266,"text":"The sage advice from the Mounties :","depth":12},{"id":267,"text":"\" We certainly do n't recommend lighting your vehicle on fire","depth":14},{"id":268,"text":"to stay warm , ''","depth":14},{"id":269,"text":"Royal Canadian Mounted Police Cpl . Jeffrey Feist said .","depth":13},{"id":270,"text":"\" Stay inside your vehicle","depth":12},{"id":271,"text":"and call 911","depth":13},{"id":272,"text":"if you can . \"","depth":13},{"id":273,"text":"AND NOW A WORD FROM CHARLES...","depth":8},{"id":274,"text":"\" Obama ' s active agenda is dead on arrival .","depth":11},{"id":275,"text":"His polling numbers are going to hover around 40 .","depth":12},{"id":276,"text":"With that ,","depth":13},{"id":277,"text":"if you are a lame duck ,","depth":15},{"id":278,"text":"you only hold one of the two houses ,","depth":15},{"id":279,"text":"you are not going to get any run on that agenda .","depth":14},{"id":280,"text":"I do think","depth":11},{"id":281,"text":"it will be one of the great ironies","depth":12},{"id":282,"text":"that it will be Senate Democrats","depth":13},{"id":283,"text":"who drive the stake through ObamaCare ' s historic repudiation of liberals of their own singular achievement . \"","depth":13},{"id":284,"text":"-Charles Krauthammer , on \" Special Report with Bret Baier . \"","depth":9},{"id":285,"text":"Chris Stirewalt is digital politics editor for .","depth":2},{"id":286,"text":"Want First in your inbox every day ?","depth":4},{"id":287,"text":"Sign up here .","depth":4},{"id":288,"text":"To catch Chris live online daily at 11:30 a.m . ET ,","depth":4},{"id":289,"text":"click here .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":579,"left":574,"right":578,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":574,"left":426,"right":573,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":426,"left":399,"right":425,"rela